46 #define MATCH_PER_STREAM_OPT(name, type, outvar, fmtctx, st)\
47 {\
48  int i, ret;\
49  for (i = 0; i < o->nb_ ## name; i++) {\
50  char *spec = o->name[i].specifier;\
51  if ((ret = check_stream_specifier(fmtctx, st, spec)) > 0)\
52  outvar = o->name[i].u.type;\
53  else if (ret < 0)\
54  exit_program(1);\
55  }\
56 }
57 
58 #define MATCH_PER_TYPE_OPT(name, type, outvar, fmtctx, mediatype)\
59 {\
60  int i;\
61  for (i = 0; i < o->nb_ ## name; i++) {\
62  char *spec = o->name[i].specifier;\
63  if (!strcmp(spec, mediatype))\
64  outvar = o->name[i].u.type;\
65  }\
66 }

136 static void uninit_options(OptionsContext *o)
137 {
138  const OptionDef *po = options;
139  int i;
140 
141  /* all OPT_SPEC and OPT_STRING can be freed in generic way */
142  while (po->name) {
143  void *dst = (uint8_t*)o + po->u.off;
144 
145  if (po->flags & OPT_SPEC) {
146  SpecifierOpt **so = dst;
147  int i, *count = (int*)(so + 1);
148  for (i = 0; i < *count; i++) {
149  av_freep(&(*so)[i].specifier);
150  if (po->flags & OPT_STRING)
151  av_freep(&(*so)[i].u.str);
152  }
153  av_freep(so);
154  *count = 0;
155  } else if (po->flags & OPT_OFFSET && po->flags & OPT_STRING)
156  av_freep(dst);
157  po++;
158  }
159 
160  for (i = 0; i < o->nb_stream_maps; i++)
161  av_freep(&o->stream_maps[i].linklabel);
162  av_freep(&o->stream_maps);
163  av_freep(&o->audio_channel_maps);
164  av_freep(&o->streamid_map);
165  av_freep(&o->attachments);
166 }

194 /* return a copy of the input with the stream specifiers removed from the keys */
195 static AVDictionary *strip_specifiers(AVDictionary *dict)
196 {
197  AVDictionaryEntry *e = NULL;
198  AVDictionary *ret = NULL;
199 
200  while ((e = av_dict_get(dict, "", e, AV_DICT_IGNORE_SUFFIX))) {
201  char *p = strchr(e->key, ':');
202 
203  if (p)
204  *p = 0;//+: change ':' to '\0', so e->key has only option, no stream specifier
205  av_dict_set(&ret, e->key, e->value, 0);
206  if (p)
207  *p = ':';//+: recover the stream specifier
208  }
209  return ret;
210 }

275 static int opt_map(void *optctx, const char *opt, const char *arg)
276 {
277  OptionsContext *o = optctx;
278  StreamMap *m = NULL;
279  int i, negative = 0, file_idx;
280  int sync_file_idx = -1, sync_stream_idx = 0;
281  char *p, *sync;
282  char *map;
283  char *allow_unused;
284 
285  if (*arg == '-') {
286  negative = 1;
287  arg++;
288  }
289  map = av_strdup(arg);
290  if (!map)
291  return AVERROR(ENOMEM);
292 
293  /* parse sync stream first, just pick first matching stream */
294  if (sync = strchr(map, ',')) {
295  *sync = 0;
296  sync_file_idx = strtol(sync + 1, &sync, 0);
297  if (sync_file_idx >= nb_input_files || sync_file_idx < 0) {
298  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "Invalid sync file index: %d.\n", sync_file_idx);
299  exit_program(1);
300  }
301  if (*sync)
302  sync++;
303  for (i = 0; i < input_files[sync_file_idx]->nb_streams; i++)
304  if (check_stream_specifier(input_files[sync_file_idx]->ctx,
305  input_files[sync_file_idx]->ctx->streams[i], sync) == 1) {
306  sync_stream_idx = i;
307  break;
308  }
309  if (i == input_files[sync_file_idx]->nb_streams) {
310  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "Sync stream specification in map %s does not "
311  "match any streams.\n", arg);
312  exit_program(1);
313  }
314  }
315 
316 
317  if (map[0] == '[') {
318  /* this mapping refers to lavfi output */
319  const char *c = map + 1;
320  GROW_ARRAY(o->stream_maps, o->nb_stream_maps);
321  m = &o->stream_maps[o->nb_stream_maps - 1];
322  m->linklabel = av_get_token(&c, "]");
323  if (!m->linklabel) {
324  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_ERROR, "Invalid output link label: %s.\n", map);
325  exit_program(1);
326  }
327  } else {
328  if (allow_unused = strchr(map, '?'))//+: check if invalid map could be ignored
329  *allow_unused = 0;
330  file_idx = strtol(map, &p, 0);//+: get file index
331  if (file_idx >= nb_input_files || file_idx < 0) {
332  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "Invalid input file index: %d.\n", file_idx);
333  exit_program(1);
334  }
335  if (negative)
336  /* disable some already defined maps */
337  for (i = 0; i < o->nb_stream_maps; i++) {//+: like -map 0 -map -0:1, here is for the second map
338  m = &o->stream_maps[i];
339  if (file_idx == m->file_index &&
340  check_stream_specifier(input_files[m->file_index]->ctx,
341  input_files[m->file_index]->ctx->streams[m->stream_index],
342  *p == ':' ? p + 1 : p) > 0)
343  m->disabled = 1;
344  }
345  else
346  for (i = 0; i < input_files[file_idx]->nb_streams; i++) {
347  if (check_stream_specifier(input_files[file_idx]->ctx, input_files[file_idx]->ctx->streams[i],
348  *p == ':' ? p + 1 : p) <= 0)
349  continue;
350  GROW_ARRAY(o->stream_maps, o->nb_stream_maps);
351  m = &o->stream_maps[o->nb_stream_maps - 1];
352 
353  m->file_index = file_idx;
354  m->stream_index = i;
355 
356  if (sync_file_idx >= 0) {
357  m->sync_file_index = sync_file_idx;
358  m->sync_stream_index = sync_stream_idx;
359  } else {
360  m->sync_file_index = file_idx;
361  m->sync_stream_index = i;
362  }
363  }
364  }
365 
366  if (!m) {
367  if (allow_unused) {
368  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_VERBOSE, "Stream map '%s' matches no streams; ignoring.\n", arg);
369  } else {
370  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "Stream map '%s' matches no streams.\n"
371  "To ignore this, add a trailing '?' to the map.\n", arg);
372  exit_program(1);
373  }
374  }
375 
376  av_freep(&map);
377  return 0;
378 }

388 static int opt_map_channel(void *optctx, const char *opt, const char *arg)
389 {
390  OptionsContext *o = optctx;
391  int n;
392  AVStream *st;
393  AudioChannelMap *m;
394 
395  GROW_ARRAY(o->audio_channel_maps, o->nb_audio_channel_maps);
396  m = &o->audio_channel_maps[o->nb_audio_channel_maps - 1];
397 
398  /* muted channel syntax */
399  n = sscanf(arg, "%d:%d.%d", &m->channel_idx, &m->ofile_idx, &m->ostream_idx);
400  if ((n == 1 || n == 3) && m->channel_idx == -1) {
401  m->file_idx = m->stream_idx = -1;
402  if (n == 1)
403  m->ofile_idx = m->ostream_idx = -1;
404  return 0;
405  }
406 
407  /* normal syntax */
408  n = sscanf(arg, "%d.%d.%d:%d.%d",
409  &m->file_idx, &m->stream_idx, &m->channel_idx,
410  &m->ofile_idx, &m->ostream_idx);
411 
412  if (n != 3 && n != 5) {
413  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "Syntax error, mapchan usage: "
414  "[file.stream.channel|-1][:syncfile:syncstream]\n");
415  exit_program(1);
416  }
417 
418  if (n != 5) // only file.stream.channel specified
419  m->ofile_idx = m->ostream_idx = -1;
420 
421  /* check input */
422  if (m->file_idx < 0 || m->file_idx >= nb_input_files) {
423  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "mapchan: invalid input file index: %d\n",
424  m->file_idx);
425  exit_program(1);
426  }
427  if (m->stream_idx < 0 ||
428  m->stream_idx >= input_files[m->file_idx]->nb_streams) {
429  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "mapchan: invalid input file stream index #%d.%d\n",
430  m->file_idx, m->stream_idx);
431  exit_program(1);
432  }
433  st = input_files[m->file_idx]->ctx->streams[m->stream_idx];
434  if (st->codecpar->codec_type != AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO) {
435  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "mapchan: stream #%d.%d is not an audio stream.\n",
436  m->file_idx, m->stream_idx);
437  exit_program(1);
438  }
439  if (m->channel_idx < 0 || m->channel_idx >= st->codecpar->channels) {
440  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "mapchan: invalid audio channel #%d.%d.%d\n",
441  m->file_idx, m->stream_idx, m->channel_idx);
442  exit_program(1);
443  }
444  return 0;
445 }

465 /**
466  * Parse a metadata specifier passed as 'arg' parameter.
467  * @param arg metadata string to parse
468  * @param type metadata type is written here -- g(lobal)/s(tream)/c(hapter)/p(rogram)
469  * @param index for type c/p, chapter/program index is written here
470  * @param stream_spec for type s, the stream specifier is written here
471  */
472 static void parse_meta_type(char *arg, char *type, int *index, const char **stream_spec)
473 {
474  if (*arg) {
475  *type = *arg;
476  switch (*arg) {
477  case 'g':
478  break;
479  case 's':
480  if (*(++arg) && *arg != ':') {
481  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "Invalid metadata specifier %s.\n", arg);
482  exit_program(1);
483  }
484  *stream_spec = *arg == ':' ? arg + 1 : "";
485  break;
486  case 'c':
487  case 'p':
488  if (*(++arg) == ':')
489  *index = strtol(++arg, NULL, 0);
490  break;
491  default:
492  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "Invalid metadata type %c.\n", *arg);
493  exit_program(1);
494  }
495  } else
496  *type = 'g';
497 }

499 static int copy_metadata(char *outspec, char *inspec, AVFormatContext *oc, AVFormatContext *ic, OptionsContext *o)
500 {
501  AVDictionary **meta_in = NULL;
502  AVDictionary **meta_out = NULL;
503  int i, ret = 0;
504  char type_in, type_out;
505  const char *istream_spec = NULL, *ostream_spec = NULL;
506  int idx_in = 0, idx_out = 0;
507 
508  parse_meta_type(inspec, &type_in, &idx_in, &istream_spec);
509  parse_meta_type(outspec, &type_out, &idx_out, &ostream_spec);
510 
511  if (!ic) {
512  if (type_out == 'g' || !*outspec)
513  o->metadata_global_manual = 1;
514  if (type_out == 's' || !*outspec)
515  o->metadata_streams_manual = 1;
516  if (type_out == 'c' || !*outspec)
517  o->metadata_chapters_manual = 1;
518  return 0;
519  }
520 
521  if (type_in == 'g' || type_out == 'g')
522  o->metadata_global_manual = 1;
523  if (type_in == 's' || type_out == 's')
524  o->metadata_streams_manual = 1;
525  if (type_in == 'c' || type_out == 'c')
526  o->metadata_chapters_manual = 1;
527 
528  /* ic is NULL when just disabling automatic mappings */
529  if (!ic)
530  return 0;
531 
532 #define METADATA_CHECK_INDEX(index, nb_elems, desc)\
533  if ((index) < 0 || (index) >= (nb_elems)) {\
534  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "Invalid %s index %d while processing metadata maps.\n",\
535  (desc), (index));\
536  exit_program(1);\
537  }
538 
539 #define SET_DICT(type, meta, context, index)\
540  switch (type) {\
541  case 'g':\
542  meta = &context->metadata;\
543  break;\
544  case 'c':\
545  METADATA_CHECK_INDEX(index, context->nb_chapters, "chapter")\
546  meta = &context->chapters[index]->metadata;\
547  break;\
548  case 'p':\
549  METADATA_CHECK_INDEX(index, context->nb_programs, "program")\
550  meta = &context->programs[index]->metadata;\
551  break;\
552  case 's':\
553  break; /* handled separately below */ \
554  default: av_assert0(0);\
555  }\
556 
557  SET_DICT(type_in, meta_in, ic, idx_in);
558  SET_DICT(type_out, meta_out, oc, idx_out);
559 
560  /* for input streams choose first matching stream */
561  if (type_in == 's') {
562  for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++) {
563  if ((ret = check_stream_specifier(ic, ic->streams[i], istream_spec)) > 0) {
564  meta_in = &ic->streams[i]->metadata;
565  break;
566  } else if (ret < 0)
567  exit_program(1);
568  }
569  if (!meta_in) {
570  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "Stream specifier %s does not match any streams.\n", istream_spec);
571  exit_program(1);
572  }
573  }
574 
575  if (type_out == 's') {
576  for (i = 0; i < oc->nb_streams; i++) {
577  if ((ret = check_stream_specifier(oc, oc->streams[i], ostream_spec)) > 0) {
578  meta_out = &oc->streams[i]->metadata;
579  av_dict_copy(meta_out, *meta_in, AV_DICT_DONT_OVERWRITE);
580  } else if (ret < 0)
581  exit_program(1);
582  }
583  } else
584  av_dict_copy(meta_out, *meta_in, AV_DICT_DONT_OVERWRITE);
585 
586  return 0;
587 }

589 static int opt_recording_timestamp(void *optctx, const char *opt, const char *arg)
590 {
591  OptionsContext *o = optctx;
592  char buf[128];
593  int64_t recording_timestamp = parse_time_or_die(opt, arg, 0) / 1E6;
594  struct tm time = *gmtime((time_t*)&recording_timestamp);
595  if (!strftime(buf, sizeof(buf), "creation_time=%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S%z", &time))
596  return -1;
597  parse_option(o, "metadata", buf, options);
598 
599  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_WARNING, "%s is deprecated, set the 'creation_time' metadata "
600  "tag instead.\n", opt);
601  return 0;
602 }

604 static AVCodec *find_codec_or_die(const char *name, enum AVMediaType type, int encoder)
605 {
606  const AVCodecDescriptor *desc;
607  const char *codec_string = encoder ? "encoder" : "decoder";
608  AVCodec *codec;
609 
610  codec = encoder ?
611  avcodec_find_encoder_by_name(name) :
612  avcodec_find_decoder_by_name(name);
613 
614  if (!codec && (desc = avcodec_descriptor_get_by_name(name))) {
615  codec = encoder ? avcodec_find_encoder(desc->id) :
616  avcodec_find_decoder(desc->id);
617  if (codec)
618  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_VERBOSE, "Matched %s '%s' for codec '%s'.\n",
619  codec_string, codec->name, desc->name);
620  }
621 
622  if (!codec) {
623  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "Unknown %s '%s'\n", codec_string, name);
624  exit_program(1);
625  }
626  if (codec->type != type) {
627  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "Invalid %s type '%s'\n", codec_string, name);
628  exit_program(1);
629  }
630  return codec;
631 }
632 
633 static AVCodec *choose_decoder(OptionsContext *o, AVFormatContext *s, AVStream *st)
634 {
635  char *codec_name = NULL;
636 
637  MATCH_PER_STREAM_OPT(codec_names, str, codec_name, s, st);
638 #if DEBUG_LOGS
639  av_log(NULL,AV_LOG_DEBUG,"codec_name=%s\n",codec_name);
640 #endif
641  if (codec_name) {
642  AVCodec *codec = find_codec_or_die(codec_name, st->codecpar->codec_type, 0);
643  st->codecpar->codec_id = codec->id;
644  return codec;
645  } else
646  return avcodec_find_decoder(st->codecpar->codec_id);
647 }
648 
649 /* Add all the streams from the given input file to the global
650  * list of input streams. */
651 static void add_input_streams(OptionsContext *o, AVFormatContext *ic)
652 {
653  int i, ret;
654 
655  for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++) {
656  AVStream *st = ic->streams[i];
657  AVCodecParameters *par = st->codecpar;
658  InputStream *ist = av_mallocz(sizeof(*ist));
659  char *framerate = NULL, *hwaccel = NULL, *hwaccel_device = NULL;
660  char *hwaccel_output_format = NULL;
661  char *codec_tag = NULL;
662  char *next;
663  char *discard_str = NULL;
664  const AVClass *cc = avcodec_get_class();
665  const AVOption *discard_opt = av_opt_find(&cc, "skip_frame", NULL, 0, 0);
666 
667  if (!ist)
668  exit_program(1);
669 
670  GROW_ARRAY(input_streams, nb_input_streams);
671  input_streams[nb_input_streams - 1] = ist;
672 
673  ist->st = st;
674  ist->file_index = nb_input_files;
675  ist->discard = 1;
676  st->discard = AVDISCARD_ALL;
677  ist->nb_samples = 0;
678  ist->min_pts = INT64_MAX;
679  ist->max_pts = INT64_MIN;
680 
681  ist->ts_scale = 1.0;
682  MATCH_PER_STREAM_OPT(ts_scale, dbl, ist->ts_scale, ic, st);
683 
684  ist->autorotate = 1;
685  MATCH_PER_STREAM_OPT(autorotate, i, ist->autorotate, ic, st);
686 
687  MATCH_PER_STREAM_OPT(codec_tags, str, codec_tag, ic, st);
688  if (codec_tag) {
689  uint32_t tag = strtol(codec_tag, &next, 0);
690  if (*next)
691  tag = AV_RL32(codec_tag);
692  st->codecpar->codec_tag = tag;
693  }
694 
695  ist->dec = choose_decoder(o, ic, st);
696  ist->decoder_opts = filter_codec_opts(o->g->codec_opts, ist->st->codecpar->codec_id, ic, st, ist->dec);
697 
698  ist->reinit_filters = -1;
699  MATCH_PER_STREAM_OPT(reinit_filters, i, ist->reinit_filters, ic, st);
700 
701  MATCH_PER_STREAM_OPT(discard, str, discard_str, ic, st);
702  ist->user_set_discard = AVDISCARD_NONE;
703  if (discard_str && av_opt_eval_int(&cc, discard_opt, discard_str, &ist->user_set_discard) < 0) {
704  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_ERROR, "Error parsing discard %s.\n",
705  discard_str);
706  exit_program(1);
707  }
708 
709  ist->filter_in_rescale_delta_last = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
710 
711  ist->dec_ctx = avcodec_alloc_context3(ist->dec);
712  if (!ist->dec_ctx) {
713  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_ERROR, "Error allocating the decoder context.\n");
714  exit_program(1);
715  }
716 
717  ret = avcodec_parameters_to_context(ist->dec_ctx, par);
718  if (ret < 0) {
719  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_ERROR, "Error initializing the decoder context.\n");
720  exit_program(1);
721  }
722 
723  switch (par->codec_type) {
724  case AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO:
725  if(!ist->dec)
726  ist->dec = avcodec_find_decoder(par->codec_id);
727 #if FF_API_EMU_EDGE
728  if (av_codec_get_lowres(st->codec)) {
729  av_codec_set_lowres(ist->dec_ctx, av_codec_get_lowres(st->codec));
730  ist->dec_ctx->width = st->codec->width;
731  ist->dec_ctx->height = st->codec->height;
732  ist->dec_ctx->coded_width = st->codec->coded_width;
733  ist->dec_ctx->coded_height = st->codec->coded_height;
734  ist->dec_ctx->flags |= CODEC_FLAG_EMU_EDGE;
735  }
736 #endif
737 
738  // avformat_find_stream_info() doesn't set this for us anymore.
739  ist->dec_ctx->framerate = st->avg_frame_rate;
740 
741  ist->resample_height = ist->dec_ctx->height;
742  ist->resample_width = ist->dec_ctx->width;
743  ist->resample_pix_fmt = ist->dec_ctx->pix_fmt;
744 #if FIX_PIXEL_FORMAT
745  if(ist->resample_pix_fmt == AV_PIX_FMT_NONE){
746  av_log(NULL,AV_LOG_WARNING,"Invalid pixel format found, use yuv420p as default\n");
747  ist->resample_pix_fmt=AV_PIX_FMT_YUV420P;
748  }
749 #endif
750 
751 
752  MATCH_PER_STREAM_OPT(frame_rates, str, framerate, ic, st);
753  if (framerate && av_parse_video_rate(&ist->framerate,
754  framerate) < 0) {
755  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_ERROR, "Error parsing framerate %s.\n",
756  framerate);
757  exit_program(1);
758  }
759 
760  ist->top_field_first = -1;
761  MATCH_PER_STREAM_OPT(top_field_first, i, ist->top_field_first, ic, st);
762 
763  MATCH_PER_STREAM_OPT(hwaccels, str, hwaccel, ic, st);
764  if (hwaccel) {
765  if (!strcmp(hwaccel, "none"))
766  ist->hwaccel_id = HWACCEL_NONE;
767  else if (!strcmp(hwaccel, "auto"))
768  ist->hwaccel_id = HWACCEL_AUTO;
769  else {
770  int i;
771  for (i = 0; hwaccels[i].name; i++) {
772  if (!strcmp(hwaccels[i].name, hwaccel)) {
773  ist->hwaccel_id = hwaccels[i].id;
774  break;
775  }
776  }
777 
778  if (!ist->hwaccel_id) {
779  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "Unrecognized hwaccel: %s.\n",
780  hwaccel);
781  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "Supported hwaccels: ");
782  for (i = 0; hwaccels[i].name; i++)
783  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "%s ", hwaccels[i].name);
784  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "\n");
785  exit_program(1);
786  }
787  }
788  }
789 
790  MATCH_PER_STREAM_OPT(hwaccel_devices, str, hwaccel_device, ic, st);
791  if (hwaccel_device) {
792  ist->hwaccel_device = av_strdup(hwaccel_device);
793  if (!ist->hwaccel_device)
794  exit_program(1);
795  }
796 
797  MATCH_PER_STREAM_OPT(hwaccel_output_formats, str,
798  hwaccel_output_format, ic, st);
799  if (hwaccel_output_format) {
800  ist->hwaccel_output_format = av_get_pix_fmt(hwaccel_output_format);
801  if (ist->hwaccel_output_format == AV_PIX_FMT_NONE) {
802  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "Unrecognised hwaccel output "
803  "format: %s", hwaccel_output_format);
804  }
805  } else {
806  ist->hwaccel_output_format = AV_PIX_FMT_NONE;
807  }
808 
809  ist->hwaccel_pix_fmt = AV_PIX_FMT_NONE;
810 
811  break;
812  case AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO:
813  ist->guess_layout_max = INT_MAX;
814  MATCH_PER_STREAM_OPT(guess_layout_max, i, ist->guess_layout_max, ic, st);
815  guess_input_channel_layout(ist);
816 
817  ist->resample_sample_fmt = ist->dec_ctx->sample_fmt;
818  ist->resample_sample_rate = ist->dec_ctx->sample_rate;
819  ist->resample_channels = ist->dec_ctx->channels;
820  ist->resample_channel_layout = ist->dec_ctx->channel_layout;
821 
822  break;
823  case AVMEDIA_TYPE_DATA:
824  case AVMEDIA_TYPE_SUBTITLE: {
825  char *canvas_size = NULL;
826  if(!ist->dec)
827  ist->dec = avcodec_find_decoder(par->codec_id);
828  MATCH_PER_STREAM_OPT(fix_sub_duration, i, ist->fix_sub_duration, ic, st);
829  MATCH_PER_STREAM_OPT(canvas_sizes, str, canvas_size, ic, st);
830  if (canvas_size &&
831  av_parse_video_size(&ist->dec_ctx->width, &ist->dec_ctx->height, canvas_size) < 0) {
832  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "Invalid canvas size: %s.\n", canvas_size);
833  exit_program(1);
834  }
835  break;
836  }
837  case AVMEDIA_TYPE_ATTACHMENT:
838  case AVMEDIA_TYPE_UNKNOWN:
839  break;
840  default:
841  abort();
842  }
843 
844  ret = avcodec_parameters_from_context(par, ist->dec_ctx);
845  if (ret < 0) {
846  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_ERROR, "Error initializing the decoder context.\n");
847  exit_program(1);
848  }
849  }
850 }
851 
852 static void assert_file_overwrite(const char *filename)
853 {
854  if (file_overwrite && no_file_overwrite) {
855  fprintf(stderr, "Error, both -y and -n supplied. Exiting.\n");
856  exit_program(1);
857  }
858 
859  if (!file_overwrite) {
860  const char *proto_name = avio_find_protocol_name(filename);
861  if (proto_name && !strcmp(proto_name, "file") && avio_check(filename, 0) == 0) {
862  if (stdin_interaction && !no_file_overwrite) {
863  fprintf(stderr,"File '%s' already exists. Overwrite ? [y/N] ", filename);
864  fflush(stderr);
865  term_exit();
866  signal(SIGINT, SIG_DFL);
867  if (!read_yesno()) {
868  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "Not overwriting - exiting\n");
869  exit_program(1);
870  }
871  term_init();
872  }
873  else {
874  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "File '%s' already exists. Exiting.\n", filename);
875  exit_program(1);
876  }
877  }
878  }
879 }

881 static void dump_attachment(AVStream *st, const char *filename)
882 {
883  int ret;
884  AVIOContext *out = NULL;
885  AVDictionaryEntry *e;
886 
887  if (!st->codecpar->extradata_size) {
888  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_WARNING, "No extradata to dump in stream #%d:%d.\n",
889  nb_input_files - 1, st->index);
890  return;
891  }
892  if (!*filename && (e = av_dict_get(st->metadata, "filename", NULL, 0)))
893  filename = e->value;
894  if (!*filename) {
895  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "No filename specified and no 'filename' tag"
896  "in stream #%d:%d.\n", nb_input_files - 1, st->index);
897  exit_program(1);
898  }
899 
900  assert_file_overwrite(filename);
901 
902  if ((ret = avio_open2(&out, filename, AVIO_FLAG_WRITE, &int_cb, NULL)) < 0) {
903  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "Could not open file %s for writing.\n",
904  filename);
905  exit_program(1);
906  }
907 
908  avio_write(out, st->codecpar->extradata, st->codecpar->extradata_size);
909  avio_flush(out);
910  avio_close(out);
911 }
912 
913 //+: o: options for input files
914 static int open_input_file(OptionsContext *o, const char *filename)
915 {
916  InputFile *f;
917  AVFormatContext *ic;
918  AVInputFormat *file_iformat = NULL;
919  int err, i, ret;
920  int64_t timestamp;
921  AVDictionary **opts;
922  AVDictionary *unused_opts = NULL;
923  AVDictionaryEntry *e = NULL;
924  int orig_nb_streams; // number of streams before avformat_find_stream_info
925  char * video_codec_name = NULL;
926  char * audio_codec_name = NULL;
927  char *subtitle_codec_name = NULL;
928  char * data_codec_name = NULL;
929  int scan_all_pmts_set = 0;
930 
931  if (o->format) {
932  if (!(file_iformat = av_find_input_format(o->format))) {
933  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "Unknown input format: '%s'\n", o->format);
934  exit_program(1);
935  }
936  }
937 
938  if (!strcmp(filename, "-"))
939  filename = "pipe:";
940 
941  stdin_interaction &= strncmp(filename, "pipe:", 5) &&
942  strcmp(filename, "/dev/stdin");
943 
944  /* get default parameters from command line */
945  ic = avformat_alloc_context();
946  if (!ic) {
947  print_error(filename, AVERROR(ENOMEM));
948  exit_program(1);
949  }
950  if (o->nb_audio_sample_rate) {
951  av_dict_set_int(&o->g->format_opts, "sample_rate", o->audio_sample_rate[o->nb_audio_sample_rate - 1].u.i, 0);
952  }
953  if (o->nb_audio_channels) {
954  /* because we set audio_channels based on both the "ac" and
955  * "channel_layout" options, we need to check that the specified
956  * demuxer actually has the "channels" option before setting it */
957  if (file_iformat && file_iformat->priv_class &&
958  av_opt_find(&file_iformat->priv_class, "channels", NULL, 0,
959  AV_OPT_SEARCH_FAKE_OBJ)) {
960  av_dict_set_int(&o->g->format_opts, "channels", o->audio_channels[o->nb_audio_channels - 1].u.i, 0);
961  }
962  }
963  if (o->nb_frame_rates) {
964  /* set the format-level framerate option;
965  * this is important for video grabbers, e.g. x11 */
966  if (file_iformat && file_iformat->priv_class &&
967  av_opt_find(&file_iformat->priv_class, "framerate", NULL, 0,
968  AV_OPT_SEARCH_FAKE_OBJ)) {
969  av_dict_set(&o->g->format_opts, "framerate",
970  o->frame_rates[o->nb_frame_rates - 1].u.str, 0);
971  }
972  }
973  //+: option -s
974  if (o->nb_frame_sizes) {
975  av_dict_set(&o->g->format_opts, "video_size", o->frame_sizes[o->nb_frame_sizes - 1].u.str, 0);
976  }
977  if (o->nb_frame_pix_fmts)
978  av_dict_set(&o->g->format_opts, "pixel_format", o->frame_pix_fmts[o->nb_frame_pix_fmts - 1].u.str, 0);
979 
980  //+:here codec means decoder, because this is for input file
981  MATCH_PER_TYPE_OPT(codec_names, str, video_codec_name, ic, "v");
982  MATCH_PER_TYPE_OPT(codec_names, str, audio_codec_name, ic, "a");
983  MATCH_PER_TYPE_OPT(codec_names, str, subtitle_codec_name, ic, "s");
984  MATCH_PER_TYPE_OPT(codec_names, str, data_codec_name, ic, "d");
985 
986  ic->video_codec_id = video_codec_name ?
987  find_codec_or_die(video_codec_name , AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO , 0)->id : AV_CODEC_ID_NONE;
988  ic->audio_codec_id = audio_codec_name ?
989  find_codec_or_die(audio_codec_name , AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO , 0)->id : AV_CODEC_ID_NONE;
990  ic->subtitle_codec_id= subtitle_codec_name ?
991  find_codec_or_die(subtitle_codec_name, AVMEDIA_TYPE_SUBTITLE, 0)->id : AV_CODEC_ID_NONE;
992  ic->data_codec_id = data_codec_name ?
993  find_codec_or_die(data_codec_name, AVMEDIA_TYPE_DATA, 0)->id : AV_CODEC_ID_NONE;
994 
995  if (video_codec_name)
996  av_format_set_video_codec (ic, find_codec_or_die(video_codec_name , AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO , 0));
997  if (audio_codec_name)
998  av_format_set_audio_codec (ic, find_codec_or_die(audio_codec_name , AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO , 0));
999  if (subtitle_codec_name)
1000  av_format_set_subtitle_codec(ic, find_codec_or_die(subtitle_codec_name, AVMEDIA_TYPE_SUBTITLE, 0));
1001  if (data_codec_name)
1002  av_format_set_data_codec(ic, find_codec_or_die(data_codec_name, AVMEDIA_TYPE_DATA, 0));
1003 
1004  ic->flags |= AVFMT_FLAG_NONBLOCK;//+: Do not block when reading packets from input
1005  ic->interrupt_callback = int_cb;
1006 
1007  //+: just used for avformat_open_input, after that 'scan_all_pmts' is set to NULL
1008  if (!av_dict_get(o->g->format_opts, "scan_all_pmts", NULL, AV_DICT_MATCH_CASE)) {
1009  av_dict_set(&o->g->format_opts, "scan_all_pmts", "1", AV_DICT_DONT_OVERWRITE);
1010  scan_all_pmts_set = 1;
1011  }
1012  /* open the input file with generic avformat function */
1013  err = avformat_open_input(&ic, filename, file_iformat, &o->g->format_opts);
1014  if (err < 0) {
1015  print_error(filename, err);
1016  if (err == AVERROR_PROTOCOL_NOT_FOUND)
1017  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_ERROR, "Did you mean file:%s?\n", filename);
1018  exit_program(1);
1019  }
1020  if (scan_all_pmts_set)
1021  av_dict_set(&o->g->format_opts, "scan_all_pmts", NULL, AV_DICT_MATCH_CASE);
1022  //+: remove the same options in o->g->format_opts from o->g->codec_opts
1023  remove_avoptions(&o->g->format_opts, o->g->codec_opts);
1024  assert_avoptions(o->g->format_opts);
1025 
1026  /* apply forced codec ids */
1027  for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++)
1028  choose_decoder(o, ic, ic->streams[i]);
1029 
1030  /* Set AVCodecContext options for avformat_find_stream_info */
1031  opts = setup_find_stream_info_opts(ic, o->g->codec_opts);
1032  orig_nb_streams = ic->nb_streams;
1033 
1034  /* If not enough info to get the stream parameters, we decode the
1035  first frames to get it. (used in mpeg case for example) */
1036  ret = avformat_find_stream_info(ic, opts);
1037  if (ret < 0) {
1038  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "%s: could not find codec parameters\n", filename);
1039  if (ic->nb_streams == 0) {
1040  avformat_close_input(&ic);
1041  exit_program(1);
1042  }
1043  }
1044 
1045  if (o->start_time_eof != AV_NOPTS_VALUE) {
1046  if (ic->duration>0) {
1047  o->start_time = o->start_time_eof + ic->duration;
1048  } else
1049  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_WARNING, "Cannot use -sseof, duration of %s not known\n", filename);
1050  }
1051  timestamp = (o->start_time == AV_NOPTS_VALUE) ? 0 : o->start_time;
1052  /* add the stream start time */
1053  if (!o->seek_timestamp && ic->start_time != AV_NOPTS_VALUE)
1054  timestamp += ic->start_time;
1055 
1056  /* if seeking requested, we execute it */
1057  if (o->start_time != AV_NOPTS_VALUE) {
1058  int64_t seek_timestamp = timestamp;
1059 
1060  if (!(ic->iformat->flags & AVFMT_SEEK_TO_PTS)) {
1061  int dts_heuristic = 0;
1062  for (i=0; i<ic->nb_streams; i++) {
1063  const AVCodecParameters *par = ic->streams[i]->codecpar;
1064  if (par->video_delay)
1065  dts_heuristic = 1;
1066  }
1067  if (dts_heuristic) {
1068  seek_timestamp -= 3*AV_TIME_BASE / 23;
1069  }
1070  }
1071  ret = avformat_seek_file(ic, -1, INT64_MIN, seek_timestamp, seek_timestamp, 0);
1072  if (ret < 0) {
1073  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_WARNING, "%s: could not seek to position %0.3f\n",
1074  filename, (double)timestamp / AV_TIME_BASE);
1075  }
1076  }
1077 
1078  /* update the current parameters so that they match the one of the input stream */
1079  add_input_streams(o, ic);
1080 
1081  /* dump the file content */
1082  av_dump_format(ic, nb_input_files, filename, 0);
1083 
1084  GROW_ARRAY(input_files, nb_input_files);
1085  f = av_mallocz(sizeof(*f));
1086  if (!f)
1087  exit_program(1);
1088  input_files[nb_input_files - 1] = f;
1089 
1090  f->ctx = ic;
1091  f->ist_index = nb_input_streams - ic->nb_streams;
1092  f->start_time = o->start_time;
1093  f->recording_time = o->recording_time;
1094  f->input_ts_offset = o->input_ts_offset;
1095  f->ts_offset = o->input_ts_offset - (copy_ts ? (start_at_zero && ic->start_time != AV_NOPTS_VALUE ? ic->start_time : 0) : timestamp);
1096  f->nb_streams = ic->nb_streams;
1097  f->rate_emu = o->rate_emu;
1098  f->accurate_seek = o->accurate_seek;
1099  f->loop = o->loop;//+:correspond option stream_loop
1100  f->duration = 0;
1101  f->time_base = (AVRational){ 1, 1 };
1102 #if HAVE_PTHREADS
1103  f->thread_queue_size = o->thread_queue_size > 0 ? o->thread_queue_size : 8;
1104 #endif
1105 
1106  /* check if all codec options have been used */
1107  unused_opts = strip_specifiers(o->g->codec_opts);
1108  for (i = f->ist_index; i < nb_input_streams; i++) {
1109  e = NULL;
1110  while ((e = av_dict_get(input_streams[i]->decoder_opts, "", e,
1111  AV_DICT_IGNORE_SUFFIX)))
1112  av_dict_set(&unused_opts, e->key, NULL, 0);
1113  }
1114 
1115  e = NULL;
1116  while ((e = av_dict_get(unused_opts, "", e, AV_DICT_IGNORE_SUFFIX))) {
1117  const AVClass *class = avcodec_get_class();
1118  const AVOption *option = av_opt_find(&class, e->key, NULL, 0,
1119  AV_OPT_SEARCH_CHILDREN | AV_OPT_SEARCH_FAKE_OBJ);
1120  const AVClass *fclass = avformat_get_class();
1121  const AVOption *foption = av_opt_find(&fclass, e->key, NULL, 0,
1122  AV_OPT_SEARCH_CHILDREN | AV_OPT_SEARCH_FAKE_OBJ);
1123  if (!option || foption)
1124  continue;
1125 
1126 
1127  if (!(option->flags & AV_OPT_FLAG_DECODING_PARAM)) {
1128  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_ERROR, "Codec AVOption %s (%s) specified for "
1129  "input file #%d (%s) is not a decoding option.\n", e->key,
1130  option->help ? option->help : "", nb_input_files - 1,
1131  filename);
1132  exit_program(1);
1133  }
1134 
1135  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_WARNING, "Codec AVOption %s (%s) specified for "
1136  "input file #%d (%s) has not been used for any stream. The most "
1137  "likely reason is either wrong type (e.g. a video option with "
1138  "no video streams) or that it is a private option of some decoder "
1139  "which was not actually used for any stream.\n", e->key,
1140  option->help ? option->help : "", nb_input_files - 1, filename);
1141  }
1142  av_dict_free(&unused_opts);
1143 
1144  for (i = 0; i < o->nb_dump_attachment; i++) {
1145  int j;
1146 
1147  for (j = 0; j < ic->nb_streams; j++) {
1148  AVStream *st = ic->streams[j];
1149 
1150  if (check_stream_specifier(ic, st, o->dump_attachment[i].specifier) == 1)
1151  dump_attachment(st, o->dump_attachment[i].u.str);
1152  }
1153  }
1154 
1155  for (i = 0; i < orig_nb_streams; i++)
1156  av_dict_free(&opts[i]);
1157  av_freep(&opts);
1158 
1159  input_stream_potentially_available = 1;
1160 
1161  return 0;
1162 }

1209 static int choose_encoder(OptionsContext *o, AVFormatContext *s, OutputStream *ost)
1210 {
1211  enum AVMediaType type = ost->st->codecpar->codec_type;
1212  char *codec_name = NULL;
1213 
1214  if (type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO || type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO || type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_SUBTITLE) {
1215  MATCH_PER_STREAM_OPT(codec_names, str, codec_name, s, ost->st);
1216  if (!codec_name) {
1217  ost->st->codecpar->codec_id = av_guess_codec(s->oformat, NULL, s->filename,
1218  NULL, ost->st->codecpar->codec_type);
1219  ost->enc = avcodec_find_encoder(ost->st->codecpar->codec_id);
1220  if (!ost->enc) {
1221  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "Automatic encoder selection failed for "
1222  "output stream #%d:%d. Default encoder for format %s (codec %s) is "
1223  "probably disabled. Please choose an encoder manually.\n",
1224  ost->file_index, ost->index, s->oformat->name,
1225  avcodec_get_name(ost->st->codecpar->codec_id));
1226  return AVERROR_ENCODER_NOT_FOUND;
1227  }
1228  } else if (!strcmp(codec_name, "copy"))
1229  ost->stream_copy = 1;
1230  else {
1231  ost->enc = find_codec_or_die(codec_name, ost->st->codecpar->codec_type, 1);
1232  ost->st->codecpar->codec_id = ost->enc->id;
1233  }
1234  ost->encoding_needed = !ost->stream_copy;
1235  } else {
1236  /* no encoding supported for other media types */
1237  ost->stream_copy = 1;
1238  ost->encoding_needed = 0;
1239  }
1240 
1241  return 0;
1242 }

1244 static OutputStream *new_output_stream(OptionsContext *o, AVFormatContext *oc, enum AVMediaType type, int source_index)
1245 {
1246  OutputStream *ost;
1247  AVStream *st = avformat_new_stream(oc, NULL);
1248  int idx = oc->nb_streams - 1, ret = 0;
1249  const char *bsfs = NULL;
1250  char *next, *codec_tag = NULL;
1251  double qscale = -1;
1252  int i;
1253 
1254  if (!st) {
1255  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "Could not alloc stream.\n");
1256  exit_program(1);
1257  }
1258  //+: set pid from streamid_map
1259  //+: but why nb_streams-1<nb_streamid_map
1260  if (oc->nb_streams - 1 < o->nb_streamid_map)
1261  st->id = o->streamid_map[oc->nb_streams - 1];
1262 
1263  GROW_ARRAY(output_streams, nb_output_streams);
1264  if (!(ost = av_mallocz(sizeof(*ost))))
1265  exit_program(1);
1266  output_streams[nb_output_streams - 1] = ost;
1267 
1268  ost->file_index = nb_output_files - 1;
1269  ost->index = idx;
1270  ost->st = st;
1271  st->codecpar->codec_type = type;
1272 
1273  ret = choose_encoder(o, oc, ost);
1274  if (ret < 0) {
1275  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "Error selecting an encoder for stream "
1276  "%d:%d\n", ost->file_index, ost->index);
1277  exit_program(1);
1278  }
1279 
1280  ost->enc_ctx = avcodec_alloc_context3(ost->enc);
1281  if (!ost->enc_ctx) {
1282  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_ERROR, "Error allocating the encoding context.\n");
1283  exit_program(1);
1284  }
1285  ost->enc_ctx->codec_type = type;
1286 
1287  ost->ref_par = avcodec_parameters_alloc();
1288  if (!ost->ref_par) {
1289  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_ERROR, "Error allocating the encoding parameters.\n");
1290  exit_program(1);
1291  }
1292 
1293  if (ost->enc) {
1294  AVIOContext *s = NULL;
1295  char *buf = NULL, *arg = NULL, *preset = NULL;
1296 
1297  ost->encoder_opts = filter_codec_opts(o->g->codec_opts, ost->enc->id, oc, st, ost->enc);
1298 
1299  MATCH_PER_STREAM_OPT(presets, str, preset, oc, st);
1300  if (preset && (!(ret = get_preset_file_2(preset, ost->enc->name, &s)))) {
1301  do {
1302  buf = get_line(s);
1303  if (!buf[0] || buf[0] == '#') {
1304  av_free(buf);
1305  continue;
1306  }
1307  if (!(arg = strchr(buf, '='))) {
1308  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "Invalid line found in the preset file.\n");
1309  exit_program(1);
1310  }
1311  *arg++ = 0;
1312  av_dict_set(&ost->encoder_opts, buf, arg, AV_DICT_DONT_OVERWRITE);
1313  av_free(buf);
1314  } while (!s->eof_reached);
1315  avio_closep(&s);
1316  }
1317  if (ret) {
1318  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL,
1319  "Preset %s specified for stream %d:%d, but could not be opened.\n",
1320  preset, ost->file_index, ost->index);
1321  exit_program(1);
1322  }
1323  } else {
1324  ost->encoder_opts = filter_codec_opts(o->g->codec_opts, AV_CODEC_ID_NONE, oc, st, NULL);
1325  }
1326 
1327  ost->max_frames = INT64_MAX;
1328  MATCH_PER_STREAM_OPT(max_frames, i64, ost->max_frames, oc, st);
1329  for (i = 0; i<o->nb_max_frames; i++) {
1330  char *p = o->max_frames[i].specifier;
1331  if (!*p && type != AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO) {
1332  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_WARNING, "Applying unspecific -frames to non video streams, maybe you meant -vframes ?\n");
1333  break;
1334  }
1335  }
1336 
1337  ost->copy_prior_start = -1;
1338  MATCH_PER_STREAM_OPT(copy_prior_start, i, ost->copy_prior_start, oc ,st);
1339 
1340  MATCH_PER_STREAM_OPT(bitstream_filters, str, bsfs, oc, st);
1341  while (bsfs && *bsfs) {
1342  const AVBitStreamFilter *filter;
1343  char *bsf, *bsf_options_str, *bsf_name;
1344 
1345  bsf = av_get_token(&bsfs, ",");
1346  if (!bsf)
1347  exit_program(1);
1348  bsf_name = av_strtok(bsf, "=", &bsf_options_str);
1349  if (!bsf_name)
1350  exit_program(1);
1351 
1352  filter = av_bsf_get_by_name(bsf_name);
1353  if (!filter) {
1354  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "Unknown bitstream filter %s\n", bsf_name);
1355  exit_program(1);
1356  }
1357 
1358  ost->bsf_ctx = av_realloc_array(ost->bsf_ctx,
1359  ost->nb_bitstream_filters + 1,
1360  sizeof(*ost->bsf_ctx));
1361  if (!ost->bsf_ctx)
1362  exit_program(1);
1363 
1364  ret = av_bsf_alloc(filter, &ost->bsf_ctx[ost->nb_bitstream_filters]);
1365  if (ret < 0) {
1366  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_ERROR, "Error allocating a bitstream filter context\n");
1367  exit_program(1);
1368  }
1369 
1370  ost->nb_bitstream_filters++;
1371 
1372  if (bsf_options_str && filter->priv_class) {
1373  const AVOption *opt = av_opt_next(ost->bsf_ctx[ost->nb_bitstream_filters-1]->priv_data, NULL);
1374  const char * shorthand[2] = {NULL};
1375 
1376  if (opt)
1377  shorthand[0] = opt->name;
1378 
1379  ret = av_opt_set_from_string(ost->bsf_ctx[ost->nb_bitstream_filters-1]->priv_data, bsf_options_str, shorthand, "=", ":");
1380  if (ret < 0) {
1381  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_ERROR, "Error parsing options for bitstream filter %s\n", bsf_name);
1382  exit_program(1);
1383  }
1384  }
1385  av_freep(&bsf);
1386 
1387  if (*bsfs)
1388  bsfs++;
1389  }
1390  if (ost->nb_bitstream_filters) {
1391  ost->bsf_extradata_updated = av_mallocz_array(ost->nb_bitstream_filters, sizeof(*ost->bsf_extradata_updated));
1392  if (!ost->bsf_extradata_updated) {
1393  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "Bitstream filter memory allocation failed\n");
1394  exit_program(1);
1395  }
1396  }
1397 
1398  MATCH_PER_STREAM_OPT(codec_tags, str, codec_tag, oc, st);
1399  if (codec_tag) {
1400  uint32_t tag = strtol(codec_tag, &next, 0);
1401  if (*next)
1402  tag = AV_RL32(codec_tag);
1403  ost->st->codecpar->codec_tag =
1404  ost->enc_ctx->codec_tag = tag;
1405  }
1406 
1407  MATCH_PER_STREAM_OPT(qscale, dbl, qscale, oc, st);
1408  if (qscale >= 0) {
1409  ost->enc_ctx->flags |= AV_CODEC_FLAG_QSCALE;
1410  ost->enc_ctx->global_quality = FF_QP2LAMBDA * qscale;
1411  }
1412 
1413  MATCH_PER_STREAM_OPT(disposition, str, ost->disposition, oc, st);
1414  ost->disposition = av_strdup(ost->disposition);
1415 
1416  ost->max_muxing_queue_size = 128;
1417  MATCH_PER_STREAM_OPT(max_muxing_queue_size, i, ost->max_muxing_queue_size, oc, st);
1418  ost->max_muxing_queue_size *= sizeof(AVPacket);
1419 
1420  if (oc->oformat->flags & AVFMT_GLOBALHEADER)
1421  ost->enc_ctx->flags |= AV_CODEC_FLAG_GLOBAL_HEADER;
1422 
1423  av_dict_copy(&ost->sws_dict, o->g->sws_dict, 0);
1424 
1425  av_dict_copy(&ost->swr_opts, o->g->swr_opts, 0);
1426  if (ost->enc && av_get_exact_bits_per_sample(ost->enc->id) == 24)
1427  av_dict_set(&ost->swr_opts, "output_sample_bits", "24", 0);
1428 
1429  av_dict_copy(&ost->resample_opts, o->g->resample_opts, 0);
1430 
1431  ost->source_index = source_index;
1432  if (source_index >= 0) {
1433  ost->sync_ist = input_streams[source_index];
1434  input_streams[source_index]->discard = 0;
1435  input_streams[source_index]->st->discard = input_streams[source_index]->user_set_discard;
1436  }
1437  ost->last_mux_dts = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
1438 
1439  ost->muxing_queue = av_fifo_alloc(8 * sizeof(AVPacket));
1440  if (!ost->muxing_queue)
1441  exit_program(1);
1442 
1443  return ost;
1444 }

1446 static void parse_matrix_coeffs(uint16_t *dest, const char *str)
1447 {
1448  int i;

1450  for (i = 0;; i++) {
1451  dest[i] = atoi(p);
1452  if (i == 63)
1453  break;
1454  p = strchr(p, ',');
1455  if (!p) {
1456  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "Syntax error in matrix \"%s\" at coeff %d\n", str, i);
1457  exit_program(1);
1458  }
1459  p++;
1460  }
1461 }

1463 /* read file contents into a string */
1464 static uint8_t *read_file(const char *filename)
1465 {
1466  AVIOContext *pb = NULL;
1467  AVIOContext *dyn_buf = NULL;
1468  int ret = avio_open(&pb, filename, AVIO_FLAG_READ);
1469  uint8_t buf[1024], *str;
1470 
1471  if (ret < 0) {
1472  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_ERROR, "Error opening file %s.\n", filename);
1473  return NULL;
1474  }
1475 
1476  ret = avio_open_dyn_buf(&dyn_buf);
1477  if (ret < 0) {
1478  avio_closep(&pb);
1479  return NULL;
1480  }
1481  while ((ret = avio_read(pb, buf, sizeof(buf))) > 0)
1482  avio_write(dyn_buf, buf, ret);
1483  avio_w8(dyn_buf, 0);
1484  avio_closep(&pb);
1485 
1486  ret = avio_close_dyn_buf(dyn_buf, &str);
1487  if (ret < 0)
1488  return NULL;
1489  return str;
1490 }

1526 static OutputStream *new_video_stream(OptionsContext *o, AVFormatContext *oc, int source_index)
1527 {
1528  AVStream *st;
1529  OutputStream *ost;
1530  AVCodecContext *video_enc;
1531  char *frame_rate = NULL, *frame_aspect_ratio = NULL;
1532 
1533  ost = new_output_stream(o, oc, AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO, source_index);
1534  st = ost->st;
1535  video_enc = ost->enc_ctx;
1536 
1537  MATCH_PER_STREAM_OPT(frame_rates, str, frame_rate, oc, st);
1538  if (frame_rate && av_parse_video_rate(&ost->frame_rate, frame_rate) < 0) {
1539  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "Invalid framerate value: %s\n", frame_rate);
1540  exit_program(1);
1541  }
1542  if (frame_rate && video_sync_method == VSYNC_PASSTHROUGH)
1543  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_ERROR, "Using -vsync 0 and -r can produce invalid output files\n");
1544 
1545  MATCH_PER_STREAM_OPT(frame_aspect_ratios, str, frame_aspect_ratio, oc, st);
1546  if (frame_aspect_ratio) {
1547  AVRational q;
1548  if (av_parse_ratio(&q, frame_aspect_ratio, 255, 0, NULL) < 0 ||
1549  q.num <= 0 || q.den <= 0) {
1550  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "Invalid aspect ratio: %s\n", frame_aspect_ratio);
1551  exit_program(1);
1552  }
1553  ost->frame_aspect_ratio = q;
1554  }
1555 
1556  MATCH_PER_STREAM_OPT(filter_scripts, str, ost->filters_script, oc, st);
1557  MATCH_PER_STREAM_OPT(filters, str, ost->filters, oc, st);
1558 
1559  if (!ost->stream_copy) {
1560  const char *p = NULL;
1561  char *frame_size = NULL;
1562  char *frame_pix_fmt = NULL;
1563  char *intra_matrix = NULL, *inter_matrix = NULL;
1564  char *chroma_intra_matrix = NULL;
1565  int do_pass = 0;
1566  int i;
1567 
1568  MATCH_PER_STREAM_OPT(frame_sizes, str, frame_size, oc, st);
1569  if (frame_size && av_parse_video_size(&video_enc->width, &video_enc->height, frame_size) < 0) {
1570  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "Invalid frame size: %s.\n", frame_size);
1571  exit_program(1);
1572  }
1573 
1574  video_enc->bits_per_raw_sample = frame_bits_per_raw_sample;
1575  MATCH_PER_STREAM_OPT(frame_pix_fmts, str, frame_pix_fmt, oc, st);
1576  if (frame_pix_fmt && *frame_pix_fmt == '+') {
1577  ost->keep_pix_fmt = 1;
1578  if (!*++frame_pix_fmt)
1579  frame_pix_fmt = NULL;
1580  }
1581  if (frame_pix_fmt && (video_enc->pix_fmt = av_get_pix_fmt(frame_pix_fmt)) == AV_PIX_FMT_NONE) {
1582  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "Unknown pixel format requested: %s.\n", frame_pix_fmt);
1583  exit_program(1);
1584  }
1585  st->sample_aspect_ratio = video_enc->sample_aspect_ratio;
1586 
1587  if (intra_only)
1588  video_enc->gop_size = 0;
1589  MATCH_PER_STREAM_OPT(intra_matrices, str, intra_matrix, oc, st);
1590  if (intra_matrix) {
1591  if (!(video_enc->intra_matrix = av_mallocz(sizeof(*video_enc->intra_matrix) * 64))) {
1592  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "Could not allocate memory for intra matrix.\n");
1593  exit_program(1);
1594  }
1595  parse_matrix_coeffs(video_enc->intra_matrix, intra_matrix);
1596  }
1597  MATCH_PER_STREAM_OPT(chroma_intra_matrices, str, chroma_intra_matrix, oc, st);
1598  if (chroma_intra_matrix) {
1599  uint16_t *p = av_mallocz(sizeof(*video_enc->chroma_intra_matrix) * 64);
1600  if (!p) {
1601  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "Could not allocate memory for intra matrix.\n");
1602  exit_program(1);
1603  }
1604  av_codec_set_chroma_intra_matrix(video_enc, p);
1605  parse_matrix_coeffs(p, chroma_intra_matrix);
1606  }
1607  MATCH_PER_STREAM_OPT(inter_matrices, str, inter_matrix, oc, st);
1608  if (inter_matrix) {
1609  if (!(video_enc->inter_matrix = av_mallocz(sizeof(*video_enc->inter_matrix) * 64))) {
1610  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "Could not allocate memory for inter matrix.\n");
1611  exit_program(1);
1612  }
1613  parse_matrix_coeffs(video_enc->inter_matrix, inter_matrix);
1614  }
1615 
1616  MATCH_PER_STREAM_OPT(rc_overrides, str, p, oc, st);
1617  for (i = 0; p; i++) {
1618  int start, end, q;
1619  int e = sscanf(p, "%d,%d,%d", &start, &end, &q);
1620  if (e != 3) {
1621  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "error parsing rc_override\n");
1622  exit_program(1);
1623  }
1624  video_enc->rc_override =
1625  av_realloc_array(video_enc->rc_override,
1626  i + 1, sizeof(RcOverride));
1627  if (!video_enc->rc_override) {
1628  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "Could not (re)allocate memory for rc_override.\n");
1629  exit_program(1);
1630  }
1631  video_enc->rc_override[i].start_frame = start;
1632  video_enc->rc_override[i].end_frame = end;
1633  if (q > 0) {
1634  video_enc->rc_override[i].qscale = q;
1635  video_enc->rc_override[i].quality_factor = 1.0;
1636  }
1637  else {
1638  video_enc->rc_override[i].qscale = 0;
1639  video_enc->rc_override[i].quality_factor = -q/100.0;
1640  }
1641  p = strchr(p, '/');
1642  if (p) p++;
1643  }
1644  video_enc->rc_override_count = i;
1645 
1646  if (do_psnr)
1647  video_enc->flags|= AV_CODEC_FLAG_PSNR;
1648 
1649  /* two pass mode */
1650  MATCH_PER_STREAM_OPT(pass, i, do_pass, oc, st);
1651  if (do_pass) {
1652  if (do_pass & 1) {
1653  video_enc->flags |= AV_CODEC_FLAG_PASS1;
1654  av_dict_set(&ost->encoder_opts, "flags", "+pass1", AV_DICT_APPEND);
1655  }
1656  if (do_pass & 2) {
1657  video_enc->flags |= AV_CODEC_FLAG_PASS2;
1658  av_dict_set(&ost->encoder_opts, "flags", "+pass2", AV_DICT_APPEND);
1659  }
1660  }
1661 
1662  MATCH_PER_STREAM_OPT(passlogfiles, str, ost->logfile_prefix, oc, st);
1663  if (ost->logfile_prefix &&
1664  !(ost->logfile_prefix = av_strdup(ost->logfile_prefix)))
1665  exit_program(1);
1666 
1667  if (do_pass) {
1668  char logfilename[1024];
1669  FILE *f;
1670 
1671  snprintf(logfilename, sizeof(logfilename), "%s-%d.log",
1672  ost->logfile_prefix ? ost->logfile_prefix :
1673  DEFAULT_PASS_LOGFILENAME_PREFIX,
1674  i);
1675  if (!strcmp(ost->enc->name, "libx264")) {
1676  av_dict_set(&ost->encoder_opts, "stats", logfilename, AV_DICT_DONT_OVERWRITE);
1677  } else {
1678  if (video_enc->flags & AV_CODEC_FLAG_PASS2) {
1679  char *logbuffer = read_file(logfilename);
1680 
1681  if (!logbuffer) {
1682  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "Error reading log file '%s' for pass-2 encoding\n",
1683  logfilename);
1684  exit_program(1);
1685  }
1686  video_enc->stats_in = logbuffer;
1687  }
1688  if (video_enc->flags & AV_CODEC_FLAG_PASS1) {
1689  f = av_fopen_utf8(logfilename, "wb");
1690  if (!f) {
1691  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL,
1692  "Cannot write log file '%s' for pass-1 encoding: %s\n",
1693  logfilename, strerror(errno));
1694  exit_program(1);
1695  }
1696  ost->logfile = f;
1697  }
1698  }
1699  }
1700 
1701  MATCH_PER_STREAM_OPT(forced_key_frames, str, ost->forced_keyframes, oc, st);
1702  if (ost->forced_keyframes)
1703  ost->forced_keyframes = av_strdup(ost->forced_keyframes);
1704 
1705  MATCH_PER_STREAM_OPT(force_fps, i, ost->force_fps, oc, st);
1706 
1707  ost->top_field_first = -1;
1708  MATCH_PER_STREAM_OPT(top_field_first, i, ost->top_field_first, oc, st);
1709 
1710 
1711  ost->avfilter = get_ost_filters(o, oc, ost);
1712  if (!ost->avfilter)
1713  exit_program(1);
1714  } else {
1715  MATCH_PER_STREAM_OPT(copy_initial_nonkeyframes, i, ost->copy_initial_nonkeyframes, oc ,st);
1716  }
1717 
1718  if (ost->stream_copy)
1719  check_streamcopy_filters(o, oc, ost, AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO);
1720 
1721  return ost;
1722 }

1724 static OutputStream *new_audio_stream(OptionsContext *o, AVFormatContext *oc, int source_index)

1769  ist = NULL;

1775  ist = input_streams[ost->source_index];
1776  }

1780  ost->audio_channels_mapped + 1,
1781  sizeof(*ost->audio_channels_map)
1782  ) < 0 )
1783  exit_program(1);
1784

1786  }
1787  }
1788  }
1789  }
1790

1858 //+: store stream id (pid) to streamid_map

1882 static int copy_chapters(InputFile *ifile, OutputFile *ofile, int copy_metadata)
1883 {
1884  AVFormatContext *is = ifile->ctx;
1885  AVFormatContext *os = ofile->ctx;
1886  AVChapter **tmp;
1887  int i;
1888 
1889  tmp = av_realloc_f(os->chapters, is->nb_chapters + os->nb_chapters, sizeof(*os->chapters));
1890  if (!tmp)
1891  return AVERROR(ENOMEM);
1892  os->chapters = tmp;
1893 
1894  for (i = 0; i < is->nb_chapters; i++) {
1895  AVChapter *in_ch = is->chapters[i], *out_ch;
1896  int64_t start_time = (ofile->start_time == AV_NOPTS_VALUE) ? 0 : ofile->start_time;
1897  int64_t ts_off = av_rescale_q(start_time - ifile->ts_offset,
1898  AV_TIME_BASE_Q, in_ch->time_base);
1899  int64_t rt = (ofile->recording_time == INT64_MAX) ? INT64_MAX :
1900  av_rescale_q(ofile->recording_time, AV_TIME_BASE_Q, in_ch->time_base);
1901 
1902 
1903  if (in_ch->end < ts_off)
1904  continue;
1905  if (rt != INT64_MAX && in_ch->start > rt + ts_off)
1906  break;
1907 
1908  out_ch = av_mallocz(sizeof(AVChapter));
1909  if (!out_ch)
1910  return AVERROR(ENOMEM);
1911 
1912  out_ch->id = in_ch->id;
1913  out_ch->time_base = in_ch->time_base;
1914  out_ch->start = FFMAX(0, in_ch->start - ts_off);
1915  out_ch->end = FFMIN(rt, in_ch->end - ts_off);
1916 
1917  if (copy_metadata)
1918  av_dict_copy(&out_ch->metadata, in_ch->metadata, 0);
1919 
1920  os->chapters[os->nb_chapters++] = out_ch;
1921  }
1922  return 0;
1923 }

1925 static int read_ffserver_streams(OptionsContext *o, AVFormatContext *s, const char *filename)
1926 {
1927  int i, err;
1928  AVFormatContext *ic = avformat_alloc_context();
1929 
1930  ic->interrupt_callback = int_cb;
1931  err = avformat_open_input(&ic, filename, NULL, NULL);
1932  if (err < 0)
1933  return err;
1934  /* copy stream format */
1935  for(i=0;i<ic->nb_streams;i++) {
1936  AVStream *st;
1937  OutputStream *ost;
1938  AVCodec *codec;
1939  const char *enc_config;
1940 
1941  codec = avcodec_find_encoder(ic->streams[i]->codecpar->codec_id);
1942  if (!codec) {
1943  av_log(s, AV_LOG_ERROR, "no encoder found for codec id %i\n", ic->streams[i]->codecpar->codec_id);
1944  return AVERROR(EINVAL);
1945  }
1946  if (codec->type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO)
1947  opt_audio_codec(o, "c:a", codec->name);
1948  else if (codec->type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO)
1949  opt_video_codec(o, "c:v", codec->name);
1950  ost = new_output_stream(o, s, codec->type, -1);
1951  st = ost->st;
1952 
1953  avcodec_get_context_defaults3(st->codec, codec);
1954  enc_config = av_stream_get_recommended_encoder_configuration(ic->streams[i]);
1955  if (enc_config) {
1956  AVDictionary *opts = NULL;
1957  av_dict_parse_string(&opts, enc_config, "=", ",", 0);
1958  av_opt_set_dict2(st->codec, &opts, AV_OPT_SEARCH_CHILDREN);
1959  av_dict_free(&opts);
1960  }
1961 
1962  if (st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO && !ost->stream_copy)
1963  choose_sample_fmt(st, codec);
1964  else if (st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO && !ost->stream_copy)
1965  choose_pixel_fmt(st, st->codec, codec, st->codecpar->format);
1966  avcodec_copy_context(ost->enc_ctx, st->codec);
1967  if (enc_config)
1968  av_dict_parse_string(&ost->encoder_opts, enc_config, "=", ",", 0);
1969  }
1970 
1971  avformat_close_input(&ic);
1972  return err;
1973 }

2721 static int opt_target(void *optctx, const char *opt, const char *arg)
2722 {
2723  OptionsContext *o = optctx;
2724  enum { PAL, NTSC, FILM, UNKNOWN } norm = UNKNOWN;
2725  static const char *const frame_rates[] = { "25", "30000/1001", "24000/1001" };
2726 
2727  if (!strncmp(arg, "pal-", 4)) {
2728  norm = PAL;
2729  arg += 4;
2730  } else if (!strncmp(arg, "ntsc-", 5)) {
2731  norm = NTSC;
2732  arg += 5;
2733  } else if (!strncmp(arg, "film-", 5)) {
2734  norm = FILM;
2735  arg += 5;
2736  } else {
2737  /* Try to determine PAL/NTSC by peeking in the input files */
2738  if (nb_input_files) {
2739  int i, j, fr;
2740  for (j = 0; j < nb_input_files; j++) {
2741  for (i = 0; i < input_files[j]->nb_streams; i++) {
2742  AVStream *st = input_files[j]->ctx->streams[i];
2743  if (st->codecpar->codec_type != AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO)
2744  continue;
2745  fr = st->time_base.den * 1000 / st->time_base.num;
2746  if (fr == 25000) {
2747  norm = PAL;
2748  break;
2749  } else if ((fr == 29970) || (fr == 23976)) {
2750  norm = NTSC;
2751  break;
2752  }
2753  }
2754  if (norm != UNKNOWN)
2755  break;
2756  }
2757  }
2758  if (norm != UNKNOWN)
2759  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_INFO, "Assuming %s for target.\n", norm == PAL ? "PAL" : "NTSC");
2760  }
2761 
2762  if (norm == UNKNOWN) {
2763  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "Could not determine norm (PAL/NTSC/NTSC-Film) for target.\n");
2764  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "Please prefix target with \"pal-\", \"ntsc-\" or \"film-\",\n");
2765  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "or set a framerate with \"-r xxx\".\n");
2766  exit_program(1);
2767  }
2768 
2769  if (!strcmp(arg, "vcd")) {
2770  opt_video_codec(o, "c:v", "mpeg1video");
2771  opt_audio_codec(o, "c:a", "mp2");
2772  parse_option(o, "f", "vcd", options);
2773 
2774  parse_option(o, "s", norm == PAL ? "352x288" : "352x240", options);
2775  parse_option(o, "r", frame_rates[norm], options);
2776  opt_default(NULL, "g", norm == PAL ? "15" : "18");
2777 
2778  opt_default(NULL, "b:v", "1150000");
2779  opt_default(NULL, "maxrate:v", "1150000");
2780  opt_default(NULL, "minrate:v", "1150000");
2781  opt_default(NULL, "bufsize:v", "327680"); // 40*1024*8;
2782 
2783  opt_default(NULL, "b:a", "224000");
2784  parse_option(o, "ar", "44100", options);
2785  parse_option(o, "ac", "2", options);
2786 
2787  opt_default(NULL, "packetsize", "2324");
2788  opt_default(NULL, "muxrate", "1411200"); // 2352 * 75 * 8;
2789 
2790  /* We have to offset the PTS, so that it is consistent with the SCR.
2791  SCR starts at 36000, but the first two packs contain only padding
2792  and the first pack from the other stream, respectively, may also have
2793  been written before.
2794  So the real data starts at SCR 36000+3*1200. */
2795  o->mux_preload = (36000 + 3 * 1200) / 90000.0; // 0.44
2796  } else if (!strcmp(arg, "svcd")) {
2797 
2798  opt_video_codec(o, "c:v", "mpeg2video");
2799  opt_audio_codec(o, "c:a", "mp2");
2800  parse_option(o, "f", "svcd", options);
2801 
2802  parse_option(o, "s", norm == PAL ? "480x576" : "480x480", options);
2803  parse_option(o, "r", frame_rates[norm], options);
2804  parse_option(o, "pix_fmt", "yuv420p", options);
2805  opt_default(NULL, "g", norm == PAL ? "15" : "18");
2806 
2807  opt_default(NULL, "b:v", "2040000");
2808  opt_default(NULL, "maxrate:v", "2516000");
2809  opt_default(NULL, "minrate:v", "0"); // 1145000;
2810  opt_default(NULL, "bufsize:v", "1835008"); // 224*1024*8;
2811  opt_default(NULL, "scan_offset", "1");
2812 
2813  opt_default(NULL, "b:a", "224000");
2814  parse_option(o, "ar", "44100", options);
2815 
2816  opt_default(NULL, "packetsize", "2324");
2817 
2818  } else if (!strcmp(arg, "dvd")) {
2819 
2820  opt_video_codec(o, "c:v", "mpeg2video");
2821  opt_audio_codec(o, "c:a", "ac3");
2822  parse_option(o, "f", "dvd", options);
2823 
2824  parse_option(o, "s", norm == PAL ? "720x576" : "720x480", options);
2825  parse_option(o, "r", frame_rates[norm], options);
2826  parse_option(o, "pix_fmt", "yuv420p", options);
2827  opt_default(NULL, "g", norm == PAL ? "15" : "18");
2828 
2829  opt_default(NULL, "b:v", "6000000");
2830  opt_default(NULL, "maxrate:v", "9000000");
2831  opt_default(NULL, "minrate:v", "0"); // 1500000;
2832  opt_default(NULL, "bufsize:v", "1835008"); // 224*1024*8;
2833 
2834  opt_default(NULL, "packetsize", "2048"); // from www.mpucoder.com: DVD sectors contain 2048 bytes of data, this is also the size of one pack.
2835  opt_default(NULL, "muxrate", "10080000"); // from mplex project: data_rate = 1260000. mux_rate = data_rate * 8
2836 
2837  opt_default(NULL, "b:a", "448000");
2838  parse_option(o, "ar", "48000", options);
2839 
2840  } else if (!strncmp(arg, "dv", 2)) {
2841 
2842  parse_option(o, "f", "dv", options);
2843 
2844  parse_option(o, "s", norm == PAL ? "720x576" : "720x480", options);
2845  parse_option(o, "pix_fmt", !strncmp(arg, "dv50", 4) ? "yuv422p" :
2846  norm == PAL ? "yuv420p" : "yuv411p", options);
2847  parse_option(o, "r", frame_rates[norm], options);
2848 
2849  parse_option(o, "ar", "48000", options);
2850  parse_option(o, "ac", "2", options);
2851 
2852  } else {
2853  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_ERROR, "Unknown target: %s\n", arg);
2854  return AVERROR(EINVAL);
2855  }
2856 
2857  av_dict_copy(&o->g->codec_opts, codec_opts, AV_DICT_DONT_OVERWRITE);
2858  av_dict_copy(&o->g->format_opts, format_opts, AV_DICT_DONT_OVERWRITE);
2859 
2860  return 0;
2861 }

2924 static int opt_preset(void *optctx, const char *opt, const char *arg)
2925 {
2926  OptionsContext *o = optctx;
2927  FILE *f=NULL;
2928  char filename[1000], line[1000], tmp_line[1000];
2929  const char *codec_name = NULL;
2930 
2931  tmp_line[0] = *opt;
2932  tmp_line[1] = 0;
2933  MATCH_PER_TYPE_OPT(codec_names, str, codec_name, NULL, tmp_line);
2934 
2935  if (!(f = get_preset_file(filename, sizeof(filename), arg, *opt == 'f', codec_name))) {
2936  if(!strncmp(arg, "libx264-lossless", strlen("libx264-lossless"))){
2937  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "Please use -preset <speed> -qp 0\n");
2938  }else
2939  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "File for preset '%s' not found\n", arg);
2940  exit_program(1);
2941  }
2942 
2943  while (fgets(line, sizeof(line), f)) {
2944  char *key = tmp_line, *value, *endptr;
2945 
2946  if (strcspn(line, "#\n\r") == 0)
2947  continue;
2948  av_strlcpy(tmp_line, line, sizeof(tmp_line));
2949  if (!av_strtok(key, "=", &value) ||
2950  !av_strtok(value, "\r\n", &endptr)) {
2951  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "%s: Invalid syntax: '%s'\n", filename, line);
2952  exit_program(1);
2953  }
2954  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_DEBUG, "ffpreset[%s]: set '%s' = '%s'\n", filename, key, value);
2955 
2956  if (!strcmp(key, "acodec")) opt_audio_codec (o, key, value);
2957  else if (!strcmp(key, "vcodec")) opt_video_codec (o, key, value);
2958  else if (!strcmp(key, "scodec")) opt_subtitle_codec(o, key, value);
2959  else if (!strcmp(key, "dcodec")) opt_data_codec (o, key, value);
2960  else if (opt_default_new(o, key, value) < 0) {
2961  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "%s: Invalid option or argument: '%s', parsed as '%s' = '%s'\n",
2962  filename, line, key, value);
2963  exit_program(1);
2964  }
2965  }
2966 
2967  fclose(f);
2968 
2969  return 0;
2970 }

3273  }

3276  term_init();

3291 
3292  /* open output files */

3294  if (ret < 0) {
3295  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "Error opening output files: ");
3296  goto fail;
3297  }
3298 
3299  /* configure the complex filtergraphs */
3300  ret = configure_complex_filters();
3301  if (ret < 0) {
3302  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "Error configuring complex filters.\n");
3303  goto fail;
3304  }
3305 
3306 fail:
3307  uninit_parse_context(&octx);
3308  if (ret < 0) {
3309  av_strerror(ret, error, sizeof(error));
3310  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_FATAL, "%s\n", error);
3311  }

3313 }

3380  argv_internal[ind++]=argv[0];
3381

3405  continue;
3406  }

3408  if (opt[0] != '-' || !opt[1] || dashdash+1 == optindex) {
3409  SET_OUTPUT(opt,optindex-1);
3410  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_DEBUG, " matched as output file.\n");

3414

3424

3426  argv_internal[ind++]=arg;
3427  continue;
3428  }

3430  // opt++;
3431

3436  if (po->flags & OPT_EXIT) {
3437  /* optional argument, e.g. -h */
3438  arg = argv[optindex++];
3439  } else if (po->flags & HAS_ARG) {
3440  GET_ARG(arg);
3441  argv_internal[ind++]=arg;
3442  if(!strcmp(po->name,"f")&&!strcmp(arg,"tee"))
3443  return FF_TEE_OUTPUT;
3444  } else {
3445  arg = "1";
3446  }
3447

3449  "argument '%s'.\n", po->name, po->help, arg);
3450  continue;
3451  }
3452 
3453  /* AVOptions */
3454  if (argv[optindex]) {
3455  ret = find_avoption(NULL, opt+1, argv[optindex]);
3456  if (ret >= 0) {
3457  argv_internal[ind++]=opt;
3458  argv_internal[ind++]=argv[optindex];
3459  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_DEBUG, " matched as AVOption '%s' with "
3460  "argument '%s'.\n", opt, argv[optindex]);
3461  optindex++;
3462  continue;
3463  } else if (ret != FFERROR_OPTION_NOT_FOUND) {
3464  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_ERROR, "Error parsing option '%s' "
3465  "with argument '%s'.\n", opt, argv[optindex]);
3466  return ret;
3467  }
3468  }
3469 
3470  /* boolean -nofoo options */
3471  if (opt[1] == 'n' && opt[2] == 'o' &&
3472  (po = find_option(options, opt + 3)) &&
3473  po->name && po->flags & OPT_BOOL) {
3474  argv_internal[ind++]=opt;
3475  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_DEBUG, " matched as option '%s' (%s) with "
3476  "argument 0.\n", po->name, po->help);
3477  continue;
3478  }
3479 
3480  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_ERROR, "Unrecognized option '%s'.\n", opt);
3481  return FFERROR_OPTION_NOT_FOUND;
3482  }
3483 
3484  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_DEBUG, "Finished splitting the commandline.\n");
3485 
3486  if(!input_cnt){
3487  return FFERROR_NO_INPUT;
3488  }
3489  else if (input_cnt>1){
3490  return FFERROR_MULTI_INPUT;
3491  }

3493  *iidx=input_ind[0];
3494  *pat=patterns[0];
3495  }

3499 // !strncmp(patterns,"rtmp:",5)||
3500 // !strncmp(patterns,"http:",5)||

3504 // }
3505

3508 // av_log(NULL,AV_LOG_ERROR,"Input is live stream, but output is not set.\n");
3509 // show_ffconvert_usage();
3510 // exit(1);
3511 // }
3512  SET_OUTPUT(DEFAULT_OUTTAG,ind);
3513  }
3514 
3515  //add -y option
3516  argv_internal[ind++]="-y";
3517 
3518  *argc_internal=ind;
3519  *output_cnt=ocnt;
